@I@ Forty weeks, then forty-two. Then the days played peekaboo. By Wednesday noon, hours kicked, and at forty-three, minutes scratched. We got a pamphlet; doctor withdrew us four as if to reassure.
Induced, the labour is said to be. Post-term, the baby is said to be. Late, the mother is said to be.
Westminster Bridge and its amber lights hazing my tears. For quick respite, wind freezes them in place. As though I need to exhibit such freedoms.
The consultant said we could be in the room. Why wasn't he? @II@ About our baby, paralysed, I would kill to stop the whine. I could kill, dare I to move, seven thousand hours of life accrued. Screams pierce ordinarily. This one's intentless, an incessant, titanic broadcast of suffering? Inaccessible, the scream-inducers lure me to paralysis against the pleaing shriek. Cease the pain and overturn the futile cries. There wasn't a champagne tap but a fast bleep.
@III@ If only I knew how to save a life, castaway on this north wing, seventh floor. Receptionists and signs donate a buzz of fame opposite. Gynae: where a whole new world of 'lap and dye,' or 'D and C' awaits diploid destiny. Obs and gynae, obs and gynae, obs and gynae. Obs and gynae, sobs and gynae, sobs and gynae.
